CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 23, 1955, pg. 6, reads: "Brush Fire at Reservoir - Warm spring weather, accented by a blazing sun which set aflame dead vegetation still lingering from last fall, caused many brush fires in the city during the past week, among them this fire at the Herron Hill Reservoir Monday which was quickly quenched by firemen from Wandless Street Fire Street. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Fire fighters from Engine Company no. 26 fighting brush fire on side of Herron Hill Reservoir
